        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Set 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date></p>
			<p>Dear Friend <addressee>Isaac</addressee>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I again trouble you&#44; with<lb/> a few lines&#44; to inquire if I&#44; cannot have my<lb/> Books for <hi rend="underline">Roshashona</hi>&#44; as I have only one book for<lb/> those days&#59; if they cannot be completed by then<lb/> if you have any with <persName>Theodore Seixsas</persName>&#44; can I have<lb/> them <sic>untill</sic> mine&#44; are ready&#63;&#8212;are you coming<lb/> on soon&#44; I suppose not if report says true<lb/> you are better employed attending your <hi rend="underline">new</hi> flame<lb/> <persName>Mrs D C Levy&#39;s</persName> sister&#44; you are a cunning fellow and<lb/> mean to take us by surprise&#44; but that you&#39;ll<lb/> never do with me for I am always expecting<lb/> some such event for I well know you will marry<lb/> when you see the <hi rend="underline">miss right</hi> or the right miss&#8212;I will not send<lb/> you any more commissions&#44; as Love&#44; regards &#38;c<lb/> since I meet with no return&#8212;I had the<lb/> pleasure of a visit from <persName>Andrew Cohen</persName>&#44; he is fine<lb/> looking and amiable young man&#8212;<persName>Theodore Florence</persName><lb/> came to see me how he has grown&#44; quite a <hi rend="underline">bean</hi><lb/> too&#8212;<persName>Eleanor</persName>&#44; &#38; <persName>Sarah</persName>&#44; are both engaged&#44; the one<lb/> to <persName>Abraham Jonas&#39;</persName> eldest son <persName>Charles</persName>&#44; and <persName>Eleanor</persName><lb/> to <persName>Henno Labatt</persName> now of <placeName>California</placeName>&#44; I am quite<lb/> satisfied with them both&#44; they are men of worth&#44;<lb/> still I do not like <persName>Eleanor&#39;s</persName> having to go to <placeName>California</placeName><lb/> but he promises to remain only 4 or 5 years&#8212;<lb/> have you heard it before&#63;  if not do not speak of</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>without you are <hi rend="underline">asked&#8212;</hi><persName>Mr Block</persName> is in <placeName>Memphis</placeName><lb/> <persName>Augustus</persName>&#44; leaves tomorrow for <placeName>Quincy</placeName>&#44; I wish you<lb/> could marry them&#59; I shall miss him greatly&#8212;<lb/> how is your health&#63; Aunty is as usual&#8212;<lb/> <persName>Rosalie</persName>&#44; remains in <placeName>Quincy</placeName> <sic>untill</sic> after the wedding<lb/> when she <persName>Sarah</persName>&#44; <persName>Eleanor</persName>&#44; &#38; <persName>Anna Philipson</persName> &#38;c go to <placeName>New<lb/> &#61;Orleans</placeName>&#8212;<persName>Rehine</persName> is at the bay of <placeName>St Louis</placeName><lb/> with <persName>Sarah Levy</persName>&#8212;write me about the<lb/> books&#8212;ever yours affectionately</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">A Block</hi></persName></p>

        </body>
